"Three members of a Mount Carmel medical flight were killed when the helicopter crashed on its way to pick up a patient in southeast Ohio on Tuesday Jan. 29, 2019. The Survival Flight Inc. helicopter was on its way from Mount Carmel Grove City hospital to pick up a patient at Holzer Meigs hospital in Pomeroy when authorities lost contact with the aircraft. The helicopter crashed near Zaleski in Vinton County at 6:55 a.m., according to federal officials. The medical team never made it to Pomeroy and were reported missing. The Ohio State Highway Patrol has identified dead as pilot Jennifer L. Topper, 34, of Sunbury; and flight nurses Bradley J. Haynes, 48, of London and Rachel L. Cunningham, 33, of Galloway. All were pronounced dead at the scene. [Ohio State Highway Patrol]",

"Three members of a Mount Carmel medical flight were killed when the helicopter crashed on its way to pick up a patient in southeast Ohio on Tuesday Jan. 29, 2019. The Survival Flight Inc. helicopter was on its way from Mount Carmel Grove City hospital to pick up a patient at Holzer Meigs hospital in Pomeroy when authorities lost contact with the aircraft. The helicopter crashed near Zaleski in Vinton County at 6:55 a.m., according to federal officials. The medical team never made it to Pomeroy and were reported missing. The Ohio State Highway Patrol has identified dead as pilot Jennifer L. Topper, 34, of Sunbury; and flight nurses Bradley J. Haynes, 48, of London and Rachel L. Cunningham, 33, of Galloway. All were pronounced dead at the scene. [Ohio State Highway Patrol]",
